(\Omega,\Sigma)
(\Gamma, \mathcal{C})
(X_{1},\mathcal{B}_{1})
(X_{2},\mathcal{B}_{2})
\Omega = X_{1}\cup X_{2}
X_{1}\cap X_{2} = \emptyset
\mathcal{B}_{1} = \{X_{1}\cap A:A\in\Sigma)
\mathcal{B}_{2} = \{X_{2}\cap A:A\in\Sigma)
f_{1}:X_{1}\to\Gamma
f_{2}:X_{2}\to\Gamma
f:=\begin{cases}f_{1} & \text{ on }X_{1}\\f_{2} & \text{ on }X_{2}\end{cases}
f:\Omega\to\Gamma
A\in \mathcal{C}
f^{-1}(A) = (X_{1}\cap f^{-1}(A))\cup (X_{2}\cap f^{-1}(A)) = \underbrace{f_{1}^{-1}(A)}_{\in \mathcal{B_{1}}}\cup \underbrace{f_{2}^{-1}(A)}_{\in\mathcal{B_{2}}}\in\Sigma.
